    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-typescript"
      }}>{`export const ACTION_INCREASE_COUNT = "ACTION_INCREASE_COUNT";
export const ACTION_SET_NAME = "ACTION_SET_NAME";
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The `}<em parentName="p">{`createActionPayload`}</em>{` has also a sibling function `}<em parentName="p">{`createAction`}</em>{` that does not take any payload. It works in a similar fashion which is that the type of the action is a unique string literal, but that time without a payload.`}</p>
    <p>{`To recap what we need to far: first, we need to create a constant that is a string literal that will be used as a unique identifier of the action. Second, we need to create a function that has a payload strongly typed by the action's type. To tidy up everything, I usually group all common action in a single object.`}</p>
